---- MODULE ClientCentric ----
------------------------------ SYNTAX ----------------------------
# Comments: TODO InitValue could be bottom (_|_)  TLA+ specifications of Client Centric Isolation Specification by Crooks et al: https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/3087801.3087802
# Comments: TLA+ specifications by Tim Soethout (tim.soethout@ing.com)  et al Automated Validation of State-Based Client-Centric Isolation with TLA++ : https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-030-67220-1_4
------------------------------ CONSTANTS ---------------------------- # The database `State` is represented by keys with corresponding values Operation == [read: Bool, key: KeyType] |-> Value  Transaction == [ops: Seq(Operation), start: TimeStamp, commit: TimeStamp] ExecutionElem == [parentState : State , transaction :Transaction, resultState: 
============================= DEFINITIONS ============================ # Definition of states and transactions WT -is- Transactions \* By convention, write operations have read state too For simplicity we store start and commit in a lookup function ExecutionElem contains the parent State (last state in execution) , transaction which is a total order of Operations Sequence. Note: this does not contain final resultState since it's not used to check Isolation Level Definition 1: s -T-> s ' \equiv [ ( k, v ) |-| (k,v)\in(S\cap S') ] => K in W_ T /\ w(K ,V) \in {Sigma} => (K, V) is a key value pair
============================= AXIOMS ============================ # Read States: from which states can the operation read it's values Definition 2 : s -*-> s ' = [ K |-| S_p(k),v ) \in E , where e is an execution of a set transactions T, and SP refers to some state in Transactions
============================= ASSUMPTIONS ============================ * all states are complete for the given transaction (ie. readStatesForEmptyTransaction contains previous keys) # Definition 5: Given Set of Transactions , their Read States . a storage system satisfies an isolation level I iff exists E executions such that forall T in transactions : CTI(T,E).
============================= ACTIONS ============================ * SerializabilityDebug (initialState,transcations) ------------------------------- # Given System State and Set of Transactions , Debug function to check serializable transaction list exists if not print all executions else fall back to normal. TxnCommitTest(transaction,execution)= > s_T' = parent state
============================= PROPOSITIONS ============================ * Serializability: given set transactions and their read states , whether or not they are serializable SATISFIES IsolationLevel (transactions) IF EXISTS E executions such that forall t in T : CTI(t,E). # Definition 5 Given a Set of Transcations And Read States. A Storage System Satisfies the given isolation level iff exists an Execution which satisfies it
============================= CONSTANTS ============================ Keys :: {KeyType} InitValue : Value Values:Set(Values) TimeStamp::Nat # initialState and transactions are read from files KeyType is a natural number between 0.. (number of keys -1). Transactions, Execution Elem's parent state result State. A storage system satisfies an isolation level I iff exists e : forall t in T: CTI(t ,e)
============================= CONSTRAINTS ============================ SerializabilitySerializable(initialState, transactions):- SATISFIES IsolationLevel (transactions). \* fall back to normal check ReadCommittedCommitTimeStampCheck(executionElem:ExecutionElem):-( execution.parentstate in initialState  /\ ~~(\exists T_i\in transactions : (\A t'\in{T} :CTI({t'}\uplus {e}.transaction) ) ).
============================= INVARIANTS ============================ * Serializability Invariant: given Set of Transactions and their read states , whether or not they are serializable SATISFIES IsolationLevel (transactions). # Definition 5 Given a set transactions, there exists an execution that satisfies the isolation level.
# Comments: InitialState is Level1 therefore passed as argument * fall back to normal check ReadCommitted Invariant : given Set of Transcations and their read states , whether or not they are serializable SATISFIES IsolationLevel (transactions). # Definition 5 Given a set transactions, there exists an execution that satisfies the isolation level.
============================= CONVENTIONS ============================ * Read Committed : if we do not commit state in initialState then it will be committed by default Writes have read states too For simplicity of exposition, write operations only update a key once Write set W_T:={K |-| w(k ,v) \in {Sigma} } .
============================= LEMMAS ============================ * SerializabilityLemma (transaction): A transaction is serializable with respect to an empty execution. # Definition 2 Read Committed Lemma : Given a state and set of transactions, the read committed isolation level exists iff there exist uncommited write operations for all previous states .
# Comments: InitialState is Level1 therefore passed as argument * fall back to normal check TransactionSatisfiesIsolationLevel (transaction , execution): - The transaction t satisfies serializability with respect ot the given isolatino level I. # Definition 5 Given a set of transactions and an Execution, whether or not it's Serializable .
============================= EXAMPLES ============================ * TransactionSatisfiesIsolationLevel Example: For this example there exists one transaction that violates the read committed isolation level with respect to given execution. # Definition 5 Given a set of transactions and an Execution, whether or not it's Serializable .
